Golovkin dominated the middle rounds while Alvarez finished with a flurry and both boxers said they were keen to fight again. Gennady Golovkin and Saul Canelo Alvarez fought to a draw in their middleweight world title bout in Las Vegas on Saturday.Kazakh Golovkin and Mexican Alvarez each got the nod from one judge, while the third declared it a 114-114 draw. Golovkin, who landed more punches overall, remains unbeaten over his career.Golovkin dominated the middle rounds while Alvarez finished with a flurry and both boxers said they were keen to fight again. Yes, of course, if the people want it, said Alvarez. Look at my belts. I m still the champion, said Golovkin. Of course I want a rematch. 